JD - 20 : 

Core Responsibilities :

Define automation use cases and requirements
- Work with the automation and solar O&M teams to understand inspection and monitoring needs, translate them into robotics/drone system requirements and propose technical solutions.

Integrate hardware and software
- Develop flight control software and integrate GPS, LiDAR, thermal cameras and other sensors. Use ROS/PX4/ArduPilot frameworks to ensure reliable navigation and data capture.

Plan and execute inspections
- Plan flight paths and robotic missions for thermal imaging and visual inspections of panels, trackers and other infrastructure while complying with DGCA/UAS 2.0 regulations. Conduct preflight checks and ensure operational safety.

Process and analyze data
- Develop scripts or leverage ML/AI models to process high resolution and thermal imagery for hotspot detection, shading analysis and fault identification. Present results to stakeholders and integrate findings into maintenance workflows.

Testing and quality assurance
- Conduct laboratory and field tests to verify performance, identify mechanical/software issues and optimize system reliability before deployment.

Maintenance & troubleshooting
- Perform regular diagnostics, firmware updates and repairs on drones and robots. Establish maintenance schedules and keep detailed logs.

Compliance & documentation
- Ensure systems meet DGCA/FAA regulations and obtain necessary certifications. Produce documentation, standard operating procedures and training material for end-users.

Innovation & research
- Stay current with advancements in robotics, UAVs and AI; evaluate new sensors and technologies; and contribute to continuous improvement initiatives and prototypes.

